<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 21 at 10:27AM EST  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...SNOW FLURRIES OR FREEZING DRIZZLE POSSIBLE IN SOME AREAS THIS
AFTERNOON...
Temperatures are expected to remain near freezing across much of
the western Carolinas and far northeast Georgia through the day.
Very light precipitation in the form of snow flurries or drizzle
may develop this afternoon. A dusting of snow accumulation may
result. Also, any drizzle at temperatures below freezing could
allow a very thin layer of ice to form on elevated surfaces.
Either the snow or ice could lead roads to become slippery in
spots, making for dangerous driving conditions during the
afternoon or evening commute. Drive with extra caution today.</description>
